<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,354,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Color darker than in apterous forms. Pronotum brown, with a transversal yellow stripe anteriorly, with width similar to that of base of head, except eyes. Thoracic sternites yellow, marked by brown, dark brown on intersegmental area. Abdominal tergites brown, darker on anterior portion; IV–VII with longitudinal yellow stripe. Venter of abdomen centrally brown, yellow on sides. Forewing brown, with area inside cells and apex whitish. Pronotum long, subpentagonal, divided into anterior and posterior lobes, with weak longitudinal median carina, and humeri slightly elevated. Anterior lobe of pronotum with a transversal row of punctuations adjacent to anterior margin; another row between anterior and posterior lobes. Posterior lobe with several punctuations and posterior angle rounded. Wings slightly passing apex of body.</paragraph>
